@NODE Wymagania "Hardware and software requirements"
@{b}What do You need to run PCBDesigner@{ub}

Program requires:

- Kickstart 3.0 or higher.
- system libraries: mathtrans, iffparse in LIBS: directory.
- @{"MUI" LINK MUI} 3.0 or higher.
- 1 MB free RAM.
- You should have a harddisk (MUI).

For comfortable work:

- 68030/28 MHz or better CPU.
- 4 MB RAM (fast-RAM).
- Colour monitor working at 640x512 resolution or higher (no lace).
- locale.library for working in languages other than English.

Program was succesfully tested on:

- A 1200 / 2 MB
- A 1200 / Blizzard 1230-IV (68030/50) / 10 MB / no FPU
- A 1200 Infinitiv / 6 MB / FPU 68882/25
- A 1200 / Blizzard 1230-III (68030/50) / 10 MB / FPU 68882/50
- A 2000 / Blizzard 2060 / 21 MB / Picasso IV + Picasso 96 software

@{fg shine}@{b}IMPORTANT!!!@{fg text}@{ub}

PCBDesigner requires at least 12 kB of stack. Keep it in mind when running
the program from shell (enter "stack 12288" command). When You change
program's icon be sure that stack size is proper. See also @{"here" LINK FAQ}.

@ENDNODE
